ammo.snowballgun_539943199.title: Safety Crew
ammo.snowballgun_539943199.description:
Hello friends.

Workplace accidents are no joke, countless Newmans have lost their lives on the job. Their screams are heard on construction sites big and small. 

Whether you're walling off a rad town or turning that 2x2 house into a 2x2 home this hoodie is says "Safey First".








Thanks to J0hn Cis0rs for all his help.

ammo.snowballgun_803894027.title: 4 Deuces Skull Mask
ammo.snowballgun_803894027.description:
Based on the popular Deuces Four Skull worn by Navy Seals, this is hand drawn on my wacom (yeah, I suck) and "carved" to look like something that would fit within the world of Rust. Wear it and kill some Rust terrorists.

NOTE TO AFTERMARKET FOLKS: 

Why so expensive?!?? Good question and here's your answer. Garry accepted this skin but, after a complaint from another skinner about it being a ripoff of the Punisher mask (it's not - it's the Four Deuces SEAL logo, which Marvel did not and DOES not own, nor can they trademark as a skull is a part of the human anatomy) took it down a short time later. The skin ended up selling 300 copies, making it EXCEPTIONALLY rare. Most people who DO own it won't sell it, but if it does appear on the market it can range from 150-300 dollars. Personally, I think that's insane, but if you invest in skins like stocks and DO see it for less than $150, grab it, hang on to it, and PROFIT!

PS: I make no money from aftermarket sales so I get nothing out of this save for the sheer joy of knowing I made the most expensive skin in the game. lol.

ammo.snowballgun_821441043.title: BoltFace Metal Facemask
ammo.snowballgun_821441043.description:
"Ooh, Shiny......quite creepy at night as well."

This is the mask of the legendary fearsome raider, whos face got terribly disfigured in an accident that happened during what seemed like a regular everyday raid.

To cut the story short: the dude opened a loot chest, without checking it for traps which set off an explosive device that embedded metallic shrapnel into his face. The unlucky guy was given a nickname by his raidmates - BoltFace.
That nickname, as well as his newly acquired facial features  greately helped him and his colleages to become the most recognized raid group. Later on, a small number of masks was made for BoltFace's most loyal followers.

If you're holding one of those masks right now, consider yourself lucky for two reasons:

1) Those masks are old and quite troublesome to obtain nowadays.

2) You didn't have to see your friend's face getting obliterated with shrapnel before you took possession of this mask.... OR DID YOU?!

ammo.snowballgun_832934294.title: Where Eagles Dare
ammo.snowballgun_832934294.description:
I got a few requests (including one from my clanmate DayZTroller) for a mask in a little something camo. I know everyone is all hating on camo right now, and there's basically camo versions of everything, but there still isn't a camo mask in the market so why not. This is a major overhaul of my Rustocalypse Mask, which got like a zillion likes and was favorited a bunch but not accepted so, seeing as how it's my thing anyway, I'm gonna recycle bits of it dammit!

If you like my stuff please [url=http://steamcommunity.com/profiles/76561197971113659/myworkshopfiles/?appid=252490]FOLLOW ME [/url]!

OH! I also promised Muzz a recipe for Paella, so here goes...AND YOU NEED A PAELLA PAN!! IF YOU DON'T USE ONE IT'S NOT PAELLA!! And this is not my recipe, but one I use ;)

INGREDIENTS
2 Tablespoons Olive Oil
1 and ½ Cups bomba rice or Arborio* (Paella rice)
3 cups chicken stock
1 onion, diced
4 cloves garlic, minced
2 tablespoons tomato paste
1 teaspoon smoked paprika
1 teaspoon saffron threads (2 pinches)
½ teaspoon turmeric
½ teaspoon red chili flakes (or 2 chili de arbol)
1 teaspoon kosher salt*
8 ounces Spanish chorizo* (the kind that is dried and cured NOT Mexican chorizo which is ground) sliced into rounds
1 pound raw shrimp
fresh chopped parsley
INSTRUCTIONS
Heat a large paella pan over medium heat. Add the olive oil. When oil is hot, add the onion and saute for 5 minutes, until onion is softened and turning golden. Add the garlic and saute for 30 seconds.
Add the tomato paste and continue to cook until it is completely mixed in and the onions are rust colored, 2- 3 minutes.
Add the salt, paprika, chili flakes, turmeric and saffron, stir to incorporate.
Add the rice and stir fry until the rice is completely coated with the oil and spices.
Stir in the stock. Bring to a simmer.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add in the sliced chorizo and cook for about 5 more minutes.
Arrange the shrimp on top. You may need to press the shrimp into the rice with a spoon so that they are almost covered with the remaining liquid. Cook for 5-10 more minutes or until liquid is evaporated.
Sprinkle parsley on top and serve.

ammo.snowballgun_861551572.title: Crimson Headwrap
ammo.snowballgun_861551572.description:
This item has been removed due to the following reasons:

The art used on this item was labelled as royalty free and free for commercial use on the website pixabay.com. I used this art on random items and it just so happened to look nice on the headwrap so I uploaded it not expecting for it to get into the game. Once it was taken down me and Garry exchanged a couple of emails about why and what was happening, the item has been removed and the art was not actually royalty free. The user who uploaded the art has now been banned from pixabay for breaching ToS

ammo.snowballgun_837149011.title: Uprising Stone Pickaxe
ammo.snowballgun_837149011.description:
"As the apocalypse hit, it became time for the aboriginals to rise again,
In the ruined world of rust where radiation plagues and where people suffer.
There were two brothers who fought side by side, which started a tribe."

These skins have been torn, worn, rusted, smudged and who knows. maybe even shit on
And yes, I'm slightly insane for making this "cinematic". But I love rendering.

Thanks to viyth for providing me with the background music and sound!

ammo.snowballgun_882451685.title: Sleazy Rider II
ammo.snowballgun_882451685.description:
THIS ITEM HAS BEEN ACCEPTED IN RUST !! BUY IT [url=http://store.steampowered.com/itemstore/252490/detail/21502/] HERE [/URL]!

This is a second stab (get it!?) at my biker jacket, Sleazy Rider. The original Sleazy had a bunch of patches on it and, to be honest, I never really dug 'em. They looked "fake" and stuck out like a sore thumb. I decided to go back in and make it rougher, take away the patches, redo the undershirt, and just make it look more "Rusty".

If you like my stuff please [url=http://steamcommunity.com/profiles/76561197971113659/myworkshopfiles/?appid=252490]FOLLOW MY WORKSHOP [/url]!

ammo.snowballgun_926184643.description:
Tanegashima were used by the samurai class and their foot soldiers (ashigaru) and within a few years the introduction of the tanegashima in battle changed the way war was fought in Japan forever.

Matchlock guns quickly supplanted the Yumi longbow in Japanese warfare thanks to their ease of use and excellent armor-penetrating qualities.

A tribal hoodie to go along with the [url=http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?source=Facepunch.Steamworks&id=939586076]Nordic Beast Pants [/url] and Nordic Beast
Street Sign Armor!

And now, a recipe for Lutefisk!!

Soak the fish in clear water for 3 days.
Add 2 tbsp lye into a gallon of water.
Soak for 3 days in this solution.
Then soak for 4 days in clear water, changing the water every day.
To cook the lute fish--------.
Tie the fish loosely in a square of cheese cloth.
Drop in a large enamel pot of boiling water.
Cook 10 minutes or until well done.
Remove cheese cloth put on a platter and debone.
Serve with a white sauce or a mustard sauce.

ammo.snowballgun_1084396407.title: Steel and Diesel Roadsign Pants
ammo.snowballgun_1084396407.description: A short armored kilt made from street signs and diesel engine parts---mostly the air conditioning and cooling components.  The parts fit well--it's heavy, but strong.

roadsign.kilt_1084396407.title: Steel and Diesel Roadsign Pants
roadsign.kilt_1084396407.description: A short armored kilt made from street signs and diesel engine parts---mostly the air conditioning and cooling components.  The parts fit well--it's heavy, but strong.

ammo.snowballgun_1084394793.title: Steel and Diesel Roadsign Vest
ammo.snowballgun_1084394793.description: A metal vest made from salvaged diesel truck parts and the backs of old road signs.  It's very heavy, but sturdy and surprisingly comfortable to wear.  Just don't go swimming in it.

roadsign.jacket_1084394793.title: Steel and Diesel Roadsign Vest
roadsign.jacket_1084394793.description: A metal vest made from salvaged diesel truck parts and the backs of old road signs.  It's very heavy, but sturdy and surprisingly comfortable to wear.  Just don't go swimming in it.

ammo.snowballgun_1084392788.title: Tailgunner Boots
ammo.snowballgun_1084392788.description: Boots belonging to a long dead pre-apocalyptic soldier, repaired with modern materials and ready for action.  The mostly artificial fibers in the boots survived well the passing decades--only a few patches and replacements were needed.

shoes.boots_1084392788.title: Tailgunner Boots
shoes.boots_1084392788.description: Boots belonging to a long dead pre-apocalyptic soldier, repaired with modern materials and ready for action.  The mostly artificial fibers in the boots survived well the passing decades--only a few patches and replacements were needed.

ammo.snowballgun_1084390180.title: Tailgunner Gloves
ammo.snowballgun_1084390180.description: Pried from the cold, dead, and mostly skeletal hands of an ancient soldier, these gloves have been washed clean of the stench of Death but branded with its mark on the their backs.

ammo.snowballgun_1092674304.title: Steel and Diesel AK47
ammo.snowballgun_1092674304.description: Some of the external parts on this old assault rifle came from a salvaged diesel engine and a truck radiator.  The inner parts are all original and in need of replacement, but more old truck parts aren't likely to help.

rifle.ak_1092674304.title: Steel and Diesel AK47

ammo.snowballgun_1092678229.title: Safe Room Door

ammo.snowballgun_1283812544.title: Spartan Warlord - Sword
ammo.snowballgun_1283812544.description:
[url=http://store.steampowered.com/itemstore/252490/detail/26504/][img]http://i.imgur.com/XqpbmUH.jpg[/img][/url]


Deep in a lost abandoned city, from a time long forgotten, amongst the ruin you find an old strange building. Through the hole in the wall you find strange artifacts and paintings that must be from a time before the old gods. While pillaging what remains of this "MUS-UM", a faint wind begins to blow and from it a faint voice calls out to you from the dark. Searching for the voice you find a rusted but functional suit of armor from a time long ago.
Equip the armor and become the warlord you were destined to be.
[url=https://www.youtube.com/user/Rchamb21/]Rcham Youtube Channel[/url]

[url=http://steamcommunity.com/id/MilhoFrito/myworkshopfiles/?appid=252490][img]https://i.imgur.com/vTDAQU3.png[/img][/url]

ammo.snowballgun_1334974046.title: Cargo Truck Garage Door
ammo.snowballgun_1334974046.description:
NEW: Check out the new matching Global Freight Crate here - https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=1686299197! 


[img]https://i.imgur.com/9Fjgh2N.png[/img]

"When it absolutely, positively, has to get to a mysterious island full of naked people overnight."

Global Freight! The number one made-up name in...err...global...uh...freight. We're not going to speculate upon whether or not this truck made it to its intended destination, but an enterprising Newman found a use for its cargo door. A little welding here, some cutouts there, and a even a repurposed "package roller" system now serving as "bars" for the windows. 

What can orange do for you?

ammo.snowballgun_1296042340.title: Brony Bag
ammo.snowballgun_1296042340.description:
What we have here is a bag o' horrors...once an innocent child's sleeping bag, this tattered old thing's been adopted by a Newman with a penchant for unicorns, rainbows, hearts, and...it's just icky, man. Icky.  This is...The Brony Bag!! It's only slightly less disturbing than the Furry Bag. Lay it outside of a raid and watch your opponents flee in abject terror at the mere prospect of coming face to face with the deviant who owns this thing! 

Mentally challenged unicorn drawn by me. You're welcome.

ammo.snowballgun_1358030533.title: Sailor's Garage Door
ammo.snowballgun_1358030533.description:
People who used to live on the Island used this type of garage door to store their boats in a secured base, through the years the garage doors all over the island got exposed to extreme weather conditions only seen on the island and nuclear radiation that led to the garage doors being all rusty and beat up looking. Luckily they were made by a special military company so newcomers coming to discover the island can reuse them as the doors still work perfectly fine.

[url=http://store.steampowered.com/itemstore/252490/detail/27103/][img]https://i.imgur.com/fNqb7za.png[/img][/url]
[url=http://steamcommunity.com/id/phase96/myworkshopfiles/][img]https://i.imgur.com/el38Bh8.png[/img][/url]

ammo.snowballgun_1461385713.title: A Car Rug! - Rust Island Edition
ammo.snowballgun_1461385713.description:
XTAB:
It’s easy to imagine this rug hung on the Cobalt conference room wall, or on the floor in the boss’s office.  A quaint company town with gas stations, super markets, nuclear reactors and orbital launch facilities, all sweetly illustrated on a cute and cozy car rug.

Unfortunately, Better Living Through Physics didn’t come out so well.  The Launch site failed, the reactor cracked and the little company town vanished ‘neath a cloud of fallout and decay, but the rug survived, still hearkening back to happier days.  Hang it on your wall or lay it on your floor, and dream of a better tomorrow.

Frank:
One of those car rugs you all remember from youth. I decided to recreate one of these car rug patterns in the theme of Rust. I have included some of my favourite and most iconic rust monuments but I couldn’t fit em all! I really went for that broken 3D and perspective feel along with the limited pallet of the real life rugs. Don’t be fooled this took ages to draw this! Its hard to adopt such a strange rug artstyle.

It has a layble attached to the ends “COBALT Souvenir” to try bring it into lore friendly zone, hope it will be enough. 
mayube at least you will get a laugh or a smirk out of it.

Cheers, leave me a vote if you like :)

ammo.snowballgun_1569952704.title: СМЭРТЬ (DBS)
ammo.snowballgun_1569952704.description:
Forgot to say translate of that words...

"СМЭРТЬ" = смерть(official russian) = death 

"XYЯНДОК" has several meanings F.E. you are reloading gun u say "хуууу-ян-дОк".

"Шо" = что = каво/кого = чаво/чяво = what. 

"Не Понел" = don't understand

P.S.  "смэрть" and "xyяндок" that words of "Glad Valakas" check in utube. 
[url=https://store.steampowered.com/itemstore/252490/detail/30600/][img]https://i.imgur.com/3p3mM6W.png[/img][/url]

ammo.snowballgun_1476013941.title: Psychosis Pump
ammo.snowballgun_1476013941.description:
Old makeshift pump shotgun which was found at junkyard and modified by a bit maniacal person.
[i]THEY want to EAT. Grin in the darkness tells me. Feed THEM.[/i]

[url=https://store.steampowered.com/itemstore/252490/detail/30803/][img]https://i.imgur.com/DgPJKQy.png[/img][/url]
[url=http://steamcommunity.com/id/estavos/myworkshopfiles/][img]https://i.imgur.com/HWRsnF6.png[/img][/url]


[i]About:[/i]
Actually this is an experiment with composition. To realize the idea, the concept of mental disorder was used, which distorts the perception of reality by a person. To all my skins, I come from the paradigm that these are the works of those characters that hypothetically can exist in the game world. According to the idea, in-game author (character), certain actions were ordered by some creature that needs to be "fed". In fact, this work is an ideological continuation of the Pathogenesis CSMG, revealing the mental state and vision of the world of the in-game author of these works. If you liked this experiment, then I will continue to disclose this character in this direction.

ammo.snowballgun_1659781652.title: Troll Daddy AK
ammo.snowballgun_1659781652.description:
[img]https://i.imgur.com/qWjezD1.jpg[/img]

A Stabby - BADtRIP collaboration - STABtRIP!    

The Troll Daddy AK-47: The Finest Choice in slapped together, shovel-based firearms. Kill yer Rusty friends and neighbors with a smile on your face!!

Now here's a recipe for Dutch Baby Pancakes:

INGREDIENTS
3  eggs
½  cup flour
½  cup milk
1  tablespoon sugar
 Pinch of nutmeg
4  tablespoons butter
Syrup, preserves, confectioners' sugar or cinnamon sugar

PREPARATION
Preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Combine eggs, flour, milk, sugar and nutmeg in a blender jar and blend until smooth. Batter may also be mixed by hand.

Place butter in a heavy 10-inch skillet or baking dish and place in the oven. As soon as the butter has melted (watch it so it does not burn) add the batter to the pan, return pan to the oven and bake for 20 minutes, until the pancake is puffed and golden. Lower oven temperature to 300 degrees and bake five minutes longer.

Remove pancake from oven, cut into wedges and serve at once topped with syrup, preserves, confectioners' sugar or cinnamon sugar.

ammo.snowballgun_1723387671.title: Furnace from Hell
ammo.snowballgun_1723387671.description:
I have come a long way to complete this work. Starting from the creation of the five bones and the simulation of the dynamics and after that I baked out inside the lower part of the furnace. That was not the end of it, my legs went numb. And I understood that I still needed to make render with volumetric light. After a lot of attempts and failures, I finally finished the work. I hope you appreciate. 

Thank you very much!

ammo.snowballgun_1759641728.title: Rust Rider Garage Door
ammo.snowballgun_1759641728.description:
[url=https://store.steampowered.com/itemstore/252490/detail/32900/] [img]https://i.imgur.com/evVPUFj.png[/img] [/url]


Updated: Normals Completely Redone, Spec Adjusted, Artwork adjusted to make dome/chopper more defined. :)


Crafted by a Vequero (A Mexican Cowboy!), this stable door reflects life of the open range in the world of Rust. Adorned with a painting of an AK-toting rider and his horse prancing in front of a distant dome as an attack helicopter is closing in, the door to Establo de Caballos (Horse Stables) protects his prized possession. 

This is all done by me, normals made by hand, "painting" featuring a lot of mixed media, a heavily modified royalty-free  "clipart" cowboy pic that I traced (and am using LEGALLY as I purchased the commercial "extended license" for from the place where I get stuff like that for my day job. Seeing as how me drawing a horse ends up looking like my Brony stuff, this is a good thing), Illustrator, and Photoshop work (as well as some really rubbish painting - such as the cowboy's gimpy arm and AK! Wooohooo!), aged to a fine Rusty vintage. 

Enjoy it with friends, like a delicious wedge of cheese. 

[img]https://i.imgur.com/GXzwcOH.gif[/img]

ammo.snowballgun_1804915784.title: Resist Garage Door
ammo.snowballgun_1804915784.description:
I was riding the T in Boston the other day and noticed the graffiti on the older sections and how dark and beat up it looked, with layers upon layers of paint and tags covering up other paint and tags until it's just a huge weirdly beautiful piece of art in its own right. 

 It made me think of Rust and, while there's a lot of graffiti stuff in the game, there's not a lot that looks like how it REALLY looks in areas that aren't as heavily trafficked (or are just downright dangerous) so I made this. 

It's a multimedia approach with a lot of painting and scribbling techniques, some overlay work of even more handwritten scribble and doodling, and just a ton of damage. You can vaguely make out the shape of a Scientist, bits of the Cobalt logo, and a lot of just random writing, with the word RESIST tagged on the bottom.

Designed and made by me. Lots of layers, stock stuff, painting, and a few Rust screenshots (for the Scientist "head") and other bits to flesh it out, then  traced and posterized. Added some assorted scribbles and shapes which are part of a Photoshop brush/action collection I have full permission and license to use commercially. WIP picture above.

wall.frame.garagedoor_1804915784.title: Resist Garage Door
wall.frame.garagedoor_1804915784.description:
I was riding the T in Boston the other day and noticed the graffiti on the older sections and how dark and beat up it looked, with layers upon layers of paint and tags covering up other paint and tags until it's just a huge weirdly beautiful piece of art in its own right. 

 It made me think of Rust and, while there's a lot of graffiti stuff in the game, there's not a lot that looks like how it REALLY looks in areas that aren't as heavily trafficked (or are just downright dangerous) so I made this. 

It's a multimedia approach with a lot of painting and scribbling techniques, some overlay work of even more handwritten scribble and doodling, and just a ton of damage. You can vaguely make out the shape of a Scientist, bits of the Cobalt logo, and a lot of just random writing, with the word RESIST tagged on the bottom.

Designed and made by me. Lots of layers, stock stuff, painting, and a few Rust screenshots (for the Scientist "head") and other bits to flesh it out, then  traced and posterized. Added some assorted scribbles and shapes which are part of a Photoshop brush/action collection I have full permission and license to use commercially. WIP picture above.

ammo.snowballgun_1882782756.title: Sheet Metal Double Door from Hell
ammo.snowballgun_1882782756.description:
#Rustober2019

Now I am working on a new collection, but how people write to me. Nobody wants a new collection and everyone wants a continuation of the collection from hell. I’m glad to try for Rust and really want my modest little house in Hapisland to not be destroed and allowed to play solo quietly on the official server, although there are so many people running around that I can’t even cut a tree. Something I moved away from the topic.
Thanks for the support, but in the near future I will not be able to sit at the computer. I hope the door is also suitable for Halloween themes. Sorry for my bad english.

[url=https://steamcommunity.com/market/listings/252490/Double%20Door%20from%20Hell][img]https://i.imgur.com/LcvygEX.png[/img][/url]
[url=https://www.artstation.com/yourseruy/albums/1155199][img]https://i.imgur.com/jdwTv1r.png[/img][/url]

ammo.snowballgun_1886876765.title: Dia De Los Muertos Garage Door
ammo.snowballgun_1886876765.description:
THANKS FOR PURCHASING! ITEM IS NO LONGER AVAILABLE FROM THE RUST ITEM STORE, BUT WILL BE AVAILABLE IN THE STEAM MARKETPLACE. 

#Rustober2019 - 

It's that time of year again, when the dead walk the Earth! It's Dia De Los Muertos!  The holiday where the dead come back for one day a year and party with the living! Have a drink with your fallen buddy's ghost while people walk around your base dressed in skull masks and carrying flowery crucifixes and light fireworks and....I don't know. It's just a spooky thing for Halloween.

Made this in Illustrator using some traceable vector bits (that I purchased legally), and totally customized and colored, then drew some stuff around that, did some Photoshop fun to it to make it painterly, etc, etc...It's basically a big collage of like 10 things, a bunch of digital trickery, and far too much of my rubbish painting/drawing. 

Groovy.

ammo.snowballgun_1929819581.title: Desert Hawk AK47 V2
ammo.snowballgun_1929819581.description:
This is a slight touch up of the other Desert Hawk i uploaded last week.
-Removed text on the back of the AK
-Cleaned the skin up (got rid of some unnecessary things)
-added more depth to the height on the magazine
-added more depth to the height on the star 
-baked the height on the wood (because i didn't do that last time)
-added more depth to the line on the stock
-overall gave the skin more height detail while keeping it simple

ammo.snowballgun_1932460590.title: Big Dreams Door
ammo.snowballgun_1932460590.description:
[url=https://steamcommunity.com/market/listings/252490/Big%20Dreams%20Door][img]https://i.imgur.com/R1PxnN7.jpg[/img][/url]

[i]"Do you have [url=https://youtu.be/ynJYx-PioZM]Big Dreams[/url]?

Painstakingly spray painted by the blistered hands of a fresh spawn, this is not your average door... or maybe it is. 

This door represents something more, something magical. A dream.

This fresh spawn has set his sights high. One day, he will soar the crests of the deadliest monuments. One day, he will heist the compound of that negligent roof camper. One day, he will make it home stacked from that crucial fight. One day, he'll get that armoured door. 

A dream will always lay within the hearts of the mighty. A dream cannot be bullied, dejected, uprooted, or overthrown.

Will you remain on the beach forever, or will you dream big?"[/i]


[h1]A collaborative project between Exenoxx & Ramsey.

❖ Ramsey on [url=https://www.youtube.com/ramsey]YouTube[/url]
❖ Ramsey on [url=https://twitter.com/Ramsey_II]Twitter[/url]

ammo.snowballgun_1966875478.title: Lucky No.8 SAR
ammo.snowballgun_1966875478.description:
It's been awhile since the horse update but I'm in cowboy mode again and felt like revisiting the old west for my first ever SAR. Here's the Lucky No. 8! Plus I'm sick of shiny new guns. Rust needs some more dirt! So here's a dirty ass lookin' gun for your face! 

He's a gamblin' man, putting his life on the line every time he steps outside, but with his good ol' Lucky No. 8 by his side....

BLAM...

Now another guy has Lucky No. 8, but have no fear, he's even LUCKIER than the last guy and...

*sound of rock crushing skull*

This naked guy, on the other hand, seems to be pretty good with a rock! Let's see how good he is with a...

*wolf eats him*

THE CIRCLE OF RUSSSSSSSSSST....

ammo.snowballgun_2012102778.title: XPOINT Tools - Large Wood Box
ammo.snowballgun_2012102778.description:
[url=https://steamcommunity.com/market/search?q=XPOINT&category_252490_itemclass%5B%5D=any&appid=252490][img]https://i.imgur.com/LcvygEX.png[/img][/url]

[h2] For test in game:  [/h2]
/wskin box.wooden.large 2012098446 - 01 Weapons Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2012101320 - 02 Ammo Box  
/wskin box.wooden.large 2012102778 - 03 Tool Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2017867878 - 04 Components Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2017869441 - 05 Medical Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2017871892 - 06 Misс Box 
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023770995 - 07 Clothes Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023776102 - 08 Armors Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023777609 - 09 Foods Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023780547 - 10 Electrical Box


[h1]Hello Again[/h1]
After a lot of work, I present you the second version of Xpoint collection, despite the fact that my first work was ignored and not reviewed. I would really like that in the game could be to sort items more beautifully and conveniently in loot room. Some people told me that my first version has not been reviewed becouse development workers don't like Hi-Tech or SciFi style in Rust. After that I decided to do a new collection, such as I can do in my old workshop in garage, where the milling machine stands. I plan to lay out 3 boxes every week, maybe then I will have more chance to be approve. If I am not right, tell me please about this in my comments or in direct messages.

[img]https://i.imgur.com/pDg0YWC.gif[/img]

 In some house that I raid, I noticed how one fool used a spin wheel to sign boxes. Below is real screenshot
[IMG] https://i.imgur.com/9KS56Tt.png [/IMG]

I think any person is pleased to play and know where what can be found. 
And everything is sorted by category.
[img]https://i.imgur.com/2o2K0b4.png[/img]

When I thought about what categories to divide, I took into account my experience of the game, both in solo and in large teams. The most difficult category was "Resourse". It is too extensive to leave it whole, because in my house there was always a separate box with coal. (there was too much left, and it is an important component).Same is "ore" and "wood"

[img]https://i.imgur.com/xSjDlGr.png[/img]


[img]https://i.imgur.com/apwtW6Q.gif[/img]

ammo.snowballgun_2041819488.title: Fresh Produce Garage Door
ammo.snowballgun_2041819488.description:
[url=https://store.steampowered.com/itemstore/252490/detail/37001/] [img]https://i.imgur.com/5PstPM8.png[/img][/url]

Sunshine Valley! The number one name in fresh, highly-hormonal fruits and vegetables! Our staff at Zenilabs Food and Science Division have found the perfect balance between Mother Nature and small, *nonlethal doses of radiation and experimental fertilizers to give you the most vibrant, delicious, and long-lasting produce ever! 

Zenilabs: Growth through Innovation! 

*In controlled double-blind lab studies. Statement is not a guarantee.

Okay, so I made another garage door because I like making garage doors. I also made this logo and loosely based it on a logo of a company in my area. Made everything but the vegetables (because I'm not going to paint vegetables that good) from scratch. Vegetables are purchased and licensed clipart that I combined into a pile and ran through some filters and then turned into vector art (and now look nothing like the photo-realistic versions they were but hey). Otherwise it's all me (as you can see by the screenshot showing about half of the layers it took to make this logo in Photoshop).

/wskin box.wooden.large 2012098446 - 01 Weapons Box

/wskin box.wooden.large 2023777609 - 09 Foods Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023780547 - 10 Electrical Box


[h1]Hello Again[/h1]
After a lot of work, I present you the second version of Xpoint collection, despite the fact that my first work was ignored and not reviewed. I would really like that in the game could be to sort items more beautifully and conveniently in loot room. Some people told me that my first version has not been reviewed becouse development workers don't like Hi-Tech or SciFi style in Rust. After that I decided to do a new collection, such as I can do in my old workshop in garage, where the milling machine stands. I plan to lay out 3 boxes every week, maybe then I will have more chance to be approve. If I am not right, tell me please about this in my comments or in direct messages.

[img]https://i.imgur.com/pDg0YWC.gif[/img]

 In some house that I raid, I noticed how one fool used a spin wheel to sign boxes. Below is real screenshot
[IMG] https://i.imgur.com/9KS56Tt.png [/IMG]

I think any person is pleased to play and know where what can be found. 
And everything is sorted by category.
[img]https://i.imgur.com/2o2K0b4.png[/img]

When I thought about what categories to divide, I took into account my experience of the game, both in solo and in large teams. The most difficult category was "Resourse". It is too extensive to leave it whole, because in my house there was always a separate box with coal. (there was too much left, and it is an important component).Same is "ore" and "wood"

[img]https://i.imgur.com/xSjDlGr.png[/img]


[img]https://i.imgur.com/apwtW6Q.gif[/img]

ammo.snowballgun_2111916381.title: uMod Fundraiser Garage Door
ammo.snowballgun_2111916381.description:
This is a Garage Door skin designed to help support the Oxide and uMod projects, with ALL of the proceeds from this skin going directly to the development team!! 

(DISCLAIMER FROM STABBY- I had to take 1% because Steam makes the uploader do that. Otherwise it all goes to uMod!)

Since January of 2014, developers such as Wulf and Calytic have been dedicating their time toward developing Oxide and uMod for Rust, and its continued development, maintainence, and support depends on you!

Now if you haven't heard of either of these projects in the past... almost decade... get out from under that rock! These projects modify what the Rust server can do, enabling the many thousands of them to provide you with all your favorite things such as kits, more resources, gamemodes, events, custom skinning, Discord integration, and much more!

But what is uMod... uMod a re-write and moderization of Oxide, with an expanded focus on universalization, standalone tools, advanced patching, additional options, extensive performance improvements, and beyond. Tl;dr... it's better than Oxide in nearly every way.

"What is Oxide" you say? Oxide is the original project dating back to 2013 for Rust Legacy, which had limited plugin support and isn't as advanced. It is currently available for download at http://umod.org, but will be replaced by uMod soon once uMod is ready for everyone to enjoy.

Skin assets are all designed by Stabby, with the exception of the Atlas figure's body, which despite modifying heavily and coloring in, an unlimited commericial license was purchased and has been presented to Facepunch as proof of ownership. The rest of the assets were created in Illustrator with some being actual in-game images from Rust turned into "cartoon" versions (i.e. Dome, Lighthouse, etc.)

[url=https://store.steampowered.com/itemstore/252490/detail/37907] [img]https://i.imgur.com/EIlzz9w.png[/img] [/url]

wall.frame.garagedoor_2111916381.title: uMod Fundraiser Garage Door
wall.frame.garagedoor_2111916381.description:
This is a Garage Door skin designed to help support the Oxide and uMod projects, with ALL of the proceeds from this skin going directly to the development team!! 

(DISCLAIMER FROM STABBY- I had to take 1% because Steam makes the uploader do that. Otherwise it all goes to uMod!)

Since January of 2014, developers such as Wulf and Calytic have been dedicating their time toward developing Oxide and uMod for Rust, and its continued development, maintainence, and support depends on you!

Now if you haven't heard of either of these projects in the past... almost decade... get out from under that rock! These projects modify what the Rust server can do, enabling the many thousands of them to provide you with all your favorite things such as kits, more resources, gamemodes, events, custom skinning, Discord integration, and much more!

But what is uMod... uMod a re-write and moderization of Oxide, with an expanded focus on universalization, standalone tools, advanced patching, additional options, extensive performance improvements, and beyond. Tl;dr... it's better than Oxide in nearly every way.

"What is Oxide" you say? Oxide is the original project dating back to 2013 for Rust Legacy, which had limited plugin support and isn't as advanced. It is currently available for download at http://umod.org, but will be replaced by uMod soon once uMod is ready for everyone to enjoy.

Skin assets are all designed by Stabby, with the exception of the Atlas figure's body, which despite modifying heavily and coloring in, an unlimited commericial license was purchased and has been presented to Facepunch as proof of ownership. The rest of the assets were created in Illustrator with some being actual in-game images from Rust turned into "cartoon" versions (i.e. Dome, Lighthouse, etc.)

[url=https://store.steampowered.com/itemstore/252490/detail/37907] [img]https://i.imgur.com/EIlzz9w.png[/img] [/url]

Support uMod and visit them at umod.org for more information!

ammo.snowballgun_2155588318.title: Raider's Cove Garage Door
ammo.snowballgun_2155588318.description:
THIS ITEM DOES NOT GLOW!!

The heat getting you down? Well dodge some bullets and head on over to Raider's Cove! It's the ramshackle water slide that puts the F in FUN (and Fracture!). Cobbled together by wood, scrap, barrels, and god knows what else, this 100 foot tall behemoth spills right out into the gorgeous, only mildly polluted and radioactive bay!!

All assets crudeley drawn/traced  by me in Illustrator and assembled in Photoshop save for the BASE drawing of the water slide shape itself, which I had to trace in Illustrator because I really hate doing 3-D curvey things (I suck at circles). I drew all over it anyway (boards, nails, cracks, etc) and made the supporting structure, etc. I bought the water slide picture anyway and have the receipt so eat me. I  based the guy's look on some kid-friendly simple drawing style I thought made it look funny, so I mimicked it (but also bought the commercial rights because it felt right, man).

Tire texture is a photograph of an actual tire I had (don't ask) that I just ran through some filters to make it look "drawn". 

Font is BADABOOMPRO  from Blambot Comics Lettering and Licensing (purchased and only $20 bucks which is really reasonable for a font). 

Also the Rust mask is the in-game icon of the Rust Mask. I just traced it and recolored it. 

Proof of commercial rights for imagery/clip-art slide thing (even though I modified the shit out if) provided to the relevant folks. 



So there. You know everything about me? 

Tell me about yourself? What's your sign? Do you like lobster? Ever been in a Turkish prison?

ammo.snowballgun_2142378618.title: Centurion Vest
ammo.snowballgun_2142378618.description:
[url=https://store.steampowered.com/itemstore/252490/detail/38500/][img]https://i.imgur.com/gbexcp0.jpg[/img][/url]
A centurion (/sɛnˈtjʊəriən/; Latin: centurio; Greek: κεντυρίων, kentyríōn or ἑκατόνταρχος, hekatóntarkhos) was a professional officer of the Roman army after the Marian reforms of 107 BC. Centurions commanded a century of around 80 legionaries. The centuries (centuriae) commanded by the centurion theoretically derive from centum ("hundred"),but that connection is now disputed. It certainly meant "company" or "tribe", but senior centurions commanded cohorts or took senior staff roles in their legion. Centurions were also found in the Roman navy.

Concept by Vertiigo 
Modeling, texturing and rendering by Cubist
2d Concept application by Veys

[h2] For test in game:  [/h2]
/wskin box.wooden.large 2012098446 - 01 Weapons Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2012101320 - 02 Ammo Box  
/wskin box.wooden.large 2012102778 - 03 Tool Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2017867878 - 04 Components Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2017869441 - 05 Medical Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2017871892 - 06.1 Misс Box v.1
/wskin box.wooden.large 2031688330 - 06.2 Misс Box v.2
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023770995 - 07 Clothes Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023776102 - 08 Armors Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023777609 - 09 Foods Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023780547 - 10 Electrical Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2031113316 - 11 Wood Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2031115553 - 12 Coal Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2031097007 - 13 Ore Box



[h1]Hello Again[/h1]
After a lot of work, I present you the second version of Xpoint collection, despite the fact that my first work was ignored and not reviewed. I would really like that in the game could be to sort items more beautifully and conveniently in loot room. Some people told me that my first version has not been reviewed becouse development workers don't like Hi-Tech or SciFi style in Rust. After that I decided to do a new collection, such as I can do in my old workshop in garage, where the milling machine stands. I plan to lay out 3 boxes every week, maybe then I will have more chance to be approve. If I am not right, tell me please about this in my comments or in direct messages.

[img]https://i.imgur.com/pDg0YWC.gif[/img]

 In some house that I raid, I noticed how one fool used a spin wheel to sign boxes. Below is real screenshot
[IMG] https://i.imgur.com/9KS56Tt.png [/IMG]

I think any person is pleased to play and know where what can be found. 
And everything is sorted by category.
[img]https://i.imgur.com/2o2K0b4.png[/img]

When I thought about what categories to divide, I took into account my experience of the game, both in solo and in large teams. The most difficult category was "Resourse". It is too extensive to leave it whole, because in my house there was always a separate box with coal. (there was too much left, and it is an important component).Same is "ore" and "wood"

[img]https://i.imgur.com/xSjDlGr.png[/img]


[img]https://i.imgur.com/apwtW6Q.gif[/img]

ammo.snowballgun_2229214032.title: Midgards Door
ammo.snowballgun_2229214032.description:
[URL=https://store.steampowered.com/itemstore/252490/detail/39503/]
[IMG]https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/779606939218810979/62C73C580E34316E179BCD54C546A3359B34BB63/[/IMG][/URL]
The wooden door is made in the style of Scandinavian mythology. It depicts the world serpent Jörmungandr.
The serpent Jörmungandr was one of three children born to the giantess Angrboda from Loki. His sister was Hel, the mistress of the underworld of the dead, and his brother was the monstrous wolf Fenrir. He lived in the world's oceans, surrounding the land of people - Midgard.
The image of the great serpent on the door meant the inaccessibility of this place and instilled fear in the eyes of the offenders.
The door is painted in the classic colors of the Viking way of life.
The presence of red was considered an indicator of high status among the Vikings.
References and Workflow:
[img] https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/1621815315185191849/4F534465353ED796E0B5AA1BAE66A301530EA13B/[/img]

ammo.snowballgun_2039982308.description:
[url=https://steamcommunity.com/market/search?q=XPOINT&category_252490_itemclass%5B%5D=any&appid=252490][img]https://i.imgur.com/LcvygEX.png[/img][/url]

[h2] For test in game:  [/h2]
/wskin box.wooden.large 2012098446 - 01 Weapons Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2012101320 - 02 Ammo Box  
/wskin box.wooden.large 2012102778 - 03 Tool Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2017867878 - 04 Components Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2017869441 - 05 Medical Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2017871892 - 06.1 Misс Box v.1
/wskin box.wooden.large 2031688330 - 06.2 Misс Box v.2
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023770995 - 07 Clothes Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023776102 - 08 Armors Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023777609 - 09 Foods Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2023780547 - 10 Electrical Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2031113316 - 11 Wood Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2031115553 - 12 Coal Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2031097007 - 13 Ore Box
/wskin box.wooden.large 2039982308 - 14 Stone Box



[h1]Hello Again[/h1]
After a lot of work, I present you the second version of Xpoint collection, despite the fact that my first work was ignored and not reviewed. I would really like that in the game could be to sort items more beautifully and conveniently in loot room. Some people told me that my first version has not been reviewed becouse development workers don't like Hi-Tech or SciFi style in Rust. After that I decided to do a new collection, such as I can do in my old workshop in garage, where the milling machine stands. I plan to lay out 3 boxes every week, maybe then I will have more chance to be approve. If I am not right, tell me please about this in my comments or in direct messages.

[img]https://i.imgur.com/pDg0YWC.gif[/img]

 In some house that I raid, I noticed how one fool used a spin wheel to sign boxes. Below is real screenshot
[IMG] https://i.imgur.com/9KS56Tt.png [/IMG]

I think any person is pleased to play and know where what can be found. 
And everything is sorted by category.
[img]https://i.imgur.com/2o2K0b4.png[/img]

When I thought about what categories to divide, I took into account my experience of the game, both in solo and in large teams. The most difficult category was "Resourse". It is too extensive to leave it whole, because in my house there was always a separate box with coal. (there was too much left, and it is an important component).Same is "ore" and "wood"

[img]https://i.imgur.com/xSjDlGr.png[/img]


[img]https://i.imgur.com/apwtW6Q.gif[/img]

ammo.snowballgun_2249242717.title: Spirit Board Box
ammo.snowballgun_2249242717.description:
#RUSTOBER2020



Note: This Skin Does Not Glow!!

NOTE: 10/20 - Noticed that my "Spirit" Planchette thing on the back of the box was reversed, so I fixed it! :)

Summon the dead this Halloween with the Spirit Board Box!  (Note how I didn't call it a Ouija. Ouija is a trademarked BRAND name they came up with for these in the 1800s. Spirit Board is the real name for 'em, and no one owns the rights to that!).

This is 100% done by me! All done in Illustrator and Photoshop using old-school Spirit Board imagery as a reference. This is the first time I've done Linocut stuff (that scratchy line thing) since art school! Guess what!? I STILL suck at it!  See reference photos above for Spirit Board Icons vs my versions of them which aren't as nice but I'm a comic book drawin' sorta guy!

I was going to put a planchette on top but it looked flat and lame so I decided to incorporate it into a "Spirit Logo" for the game. It's probably made by a subsidiary of Cobalt...who knows.

Anyway! WEEEEEEEEEEEEEE!

ammo.snowballgun_2240088463.title: Wild Spirit AR
ammo.snowballgun_2240088463.description:
We are mainly inspired by the spiritual animals of eastern mythology when designing this piece. In Chinese culture, the tiger is the king of the beasts and has been presented with a 王 (pinyin: wáng; lit.: 'king') on his forehead for centuries. According to legend, the tiger's tail would turn white when it reached the age of 500 years. In this way, the white tiger became a kind of mythological creature. It was said that the white tiger would only appear when the emperor ruled with absolute virtue, or if there was peace throughout the world. Because the color white of the Wu Xing theory also represents the west, the White Tiger became a mythological guardian of the west.

[b]This item does NOT glow in the darkness due to pvp/stealth reasons.[/b]
